        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐὰν δέ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "even",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καί",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e. in fact, actually",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; see Hartung, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Partikell",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". I. p. 132 f.) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "be separated",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (have separated herself); in this Paul is not granting something in the way of exception, as though the preceding injunction were not to be taken too strictly (which is set aside at once by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "οὐκ ἐγὼ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀλλʼ ὁ Κύρ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 7:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but he supposes a future case, which will possibly arise notwithstanding the commandment of the Lord’s just adduced. The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐὰν καί",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " therefore, with the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δέ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of antithesis, introduces, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 7:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", an occurrence which will possibly be realized in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "experience of the future",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Hermann, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[1105]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": " Viger.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " p. 834; Winer, p. 275 [E. T. 367]). This in opposition to Rückert, who maintains that the words refer to that specific case (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 7:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and mean: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "if, however, she should perhaps have already",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " separated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "herself",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " before receiving this decision; and likewise to Hofmann, who renders: if such a separation has ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "actually already taken place",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " within the church, thereby presupposing that such a thing will henceforth never take place there again.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μενέτω ἄγαμος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] assumes that her marriage is not to be looked upon as really dissolved; hence she would be guilty of adultery should she contract another union. Comp ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 19:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
